mil.navy.nrl.cmf.sousa
Class Receptor

java.lang.Object
  mil.navy.nrl.cmf.sousa.Receptor
All Implemented Interfaces:
InvocationHandler, Selectable.Handler, Serializable
public final class Receptor
extends Object
implements InvocationHandler, Selectable.Handler, Serializable

A Receptor is a dynamic cached copy of server data, which is maintained by multicast updates from the server.

handleMessage

public Serializable handleMessage(Serializable msg)
Delegate messages that arrived as Indications on the control channel to the specialized handlers in the Receptor. Return their various responses to the caller. It is expected that a ClientSideFSM will call handleMessage from its READY state implementation of handleIndication(). No other callers are expected.

Parameters:
msg - the Serializable message to be handled
Returns:
the response
